    <item>
      <title>Text length limitation, or "Why are my messages truncated ?"</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezpm/forum/general/text_length_limitation_or_why_are_my_messages_truncated</link>
      <description>The "text" column data type is "tinyblob" dy default, which is only 255 characters long.&#13;
&#13;
Since no error message is showed when the input text is longer, I had a hard time figuring why all my private messages were truncated.&#13;
&#13;
So I changed the data type for "text", which allows up to 65535 characters.</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Hypolite Petovan)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezpm/forum/general/text_length_limitation_or_why_are_my_messages_truncated</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 30 Aug 2009 16:27:32 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Re: Policy Compatibility problems with eZ Publi...</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezpm/forum/general/policy_compatibility_problems_with_ez_publish_4_1/re_policy_compatibility_problems_with_ez_publi5</link>
      <description>Like I said in my first post, I found it more simple to comment out the whole list of functions.&#13;
&#13;
With this way, you don't have to bother about giving which right to which role, as the module is treated as a whole. Either you have full access to private messaging (reading personal messages, writing new ones, manage blacklist and contact list) or you don't have access at all.</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Hypolite Petovan)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezpm/forum/general/policy_compatibility_problems_with_ez_publish_4_1/re_policy_compatibility_problems_with_ez_publi5</guid>
