    <item>
      <title>Re: Policy Compatibility problems with eZ Publi...</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezpm/forum/general/policy_compatibility_problems_with_ez_publish_4_1/re_policy_compatibility_problems_with_ez_publi4</link>
      <description>Hi,&#13;
&#13;
All you have to do to make it working is to add one line with parameter to each view declaration, in example:&#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
$ViewList['create'] = array(&#13;
    'script' =&gt; 'create.php',&#13;
    'functions' =&gt; array( 'create' ),&#13;
);&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
So to see view called "create" you need to have function called "create" :) I hope it helps.&#13;
&#13;
&lt;i&gt;Edit: I'm talking about module.php file of course&lt;/i&gt;</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Bartek Modzelewski)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezpm/forum/general/policy_compatibility_problems_with_ez_publish_4_1/re_policy_compatibility_problems_with_ez_publi4</guid>
